    <h1>MACs and Authentication</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Wikipedia &middot; <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Message_authentication_code"><img src="/reading/wikipedia.svg" alt="wp" style="display:inline;height:1em;vertical-align:-0.1em;margin-right:0.2em;"/>Message authentication code</a> &middot; CC BY-SA 4.0</p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">A <strong>message authentication code</strong> (MAC) is a short tag computed from a message and a secret key. The receiver recomputes the tag and checks it matches. If it does, the message was not tampered with and came from someone who knows the key. A hash alone is not enough: anyone can compute H(m). A MAC requires the key.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- SVG: message + key -> MAC -> tag appended to message -->
